<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF209-557-207  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 557 207.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  April 6 1989 n1150* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Problems with IBM's Tuesday announcements.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Data processing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Computer IndustryData ProcessingProduct IntroductionCustomer RelationsNewsSystem Crash.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PROBLEMS WITH IBM'S TUESDAY ANNOUNCEMENTSandM;IBM had some rather big problems with the information system it uses todisseminate news to its customers on Tuesday: seems the system was taken downover the weekend, and when it was brought up again and the first batch ofTuesday announcements was put up, the system crashed and the whole lot waslost - that sort of thing can happen to the best of us - and as soon the newsgot out that there were major announcements - because IBM sent out the pressrelease on Monday night, the story was in the Wall Street Journal on Tuesdaymorning, so everyone with a user identity number wanted to get the details atthe same time, and when they couldn't get in, kept dialling again every fiveminutes, running into 500 other people doing exactly the same thing, thuscompounding the problems further; the upshot is that customer letters on the3090-380S and new 9370s - plus the stuff that came with them - still hadn'tbeen posted by the close of play.andO;</TEXT></DOC>